				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have seen many post on how to improve this, we want that, this is bad, and this is great.
<br />

<br />
In this I have seen some great ideas and just wanted to add them together.
<br />

<br />
We are Conjurer no matter what name SOE puts on us it means the same.  We summon things.  Instead of AA’s that get then pets added hp, flurry, AC, and every other thing we should be summoning items to give to pets that should do that.
<br />

<br />
Now I know what you are thinking.  I don’t want to summon 30 more items when I log in.  Well I agree have the AA’s scale up.  So AA number 1 might summon a sword that adds HP AA number 2 might add HP and AC.  These items could then be made just for mage pets or all pets.
<br />

<br />
To me this is better then spending 20 AA points so that our ONE group spell can hit pets.  Add an AA point that has a build in DS on a belt or gloves.  As you gain level the spells could become like jeweler bag and put all the items in one bag.  Or add it right on to the pet.  This was a great post where the person said to make a UI inventory for the pet so we can see what they have.
<br />

<br />
There are a ton of good ideas that come on to these boards but get lost due to people changing the direction of the posts.  Maybe start a master list of the good ideas that people like and lock it off.<br />_________________<br />Petitioner
<br />
Arch Convoker of Bristlebane</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
