			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem with this is, again you totally make equal all magicians again.  Any mage can get all his/her spells with enough platinum in their bank account, excepting NO DROP spells.
<br />

<br />
I don't mean to demean any casual mage out there.  But I refuse to believe anyone can seriously suggest that a casual, non-raiding magician with few aa's should be able to have the same dps as a fully time/god equipped mage with max aa's.  I mean, look at rogues as an example.  A time geared rogue, wielding DoD and JTB's, versus a casual rogue wielding an epic and maybe horn of hsagra.  The dps difference is HUGE between these guys.  Yet you put the majority of pet dps upgrades in the form of summoned items, and you effectively remove any distinction between the casual mage, and the high end end-game mages.
<br />

<br />
The entire game is built around that premise.  Do the time, earn the rewards.  You look at the timesinks your VT guilds went thru, and then the timesinks your Time enabled guilds went thru, just to get at the better gear.  There's a reason that high end gear doesn't drop from the derv 1 camp.  It's just like tradeskills.  You put in the long, tedious time developing tradeskills, and eventually you're able to make more difficult combines, with items with real value.  There are tradeskill quests out there that yield very nice items.  What would the community think if all of a sudden all those combines because NO FAIL combines.  The people who put in the time developing those skills would have a fit.  And the people who hadn't put in the time would no longer ever have anything to work towards.
<br />

<br />
- Maige<br />_________________<br /><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52912>Maige Denugget</a></b>
<br />
Master of the Elements
<br />
Arch Mage of the GNOMISH kind
<br />

<br />
<i>Is this a modrod in my pocket, or am I just happy to see you?</i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
